The assets are valued at R46-million. JOHANNESBURG - The High Court has ordered that the assets of former ANC MP Vincent Smith be restrained.
The assets are valued at R46-million. Smith and Angelo Agrizzi are facing fraud and corruption charges relating to Bosasa gifts of R800,000. READ: No crime was committed, says Smith's attorney Smith was chairing parliament's portfolio committee on correctional services at the time. Bosasa was awarded contracts of more than a billion rand. Investigating Directorate spokesperson, Sindisiwe Twala, explains the restraint order. Watch the video above.